  "abstract": "The Board is publishing for comment a proposed amendment to Regulation B (Equal Credit Opportunity). The proposed amendment would eliminate the general prohibition on collecting data relating to an applicant's race, color, sex, religion, and national origin, giving creditors the option to ask applicants to provide the information on a voluntary basis. This amendment would allow data collection only; creditors still would be prohibited from considering an applicant's race, color, sex, religion, a",
